1
00:00:02,512 --> 00:00:04,581
This is heavy what I’m about to say,

2
00:00:04,581 --> 00:00:06,841
and just take it for what it’s worth:

3
00:00:06,841 --> 00:00:11,957
women are judged according 
to their capacity to endure suffering.

4
00:00:12,027 --> 00:00:14,777
[Heartbreaking Happiness]

5
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:16,810
There, I said it:

6
00:00:16,812 --> 00:00:24,072
women are judged according 
to their ability to endure suffering.

7
00:00:24,952 --> 00:00:27,948
So, we’ll think—male to female ...

8
00:00:27,948 --> 00:00:32,768
Well, women endure
the suffering of childbirth.

9
00:00:33,482 --> 00:00:36,533
[When] we think of men 
as being tough.

10
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:39,321
But, like giving birth to a child—

11
00:00:39,321 --> 00:00:43,540
that ranks up there with about
what is pain, physical pain,

12
00:00:43,540 --> 00:00:46,235
about how much physical pain
a human being can tolerate.

13
00:00:46,244 --> 00:00:48,050
That’s on an external level.

14
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:51,505
But what it’s pointing at
to endure suffering ...

15
00:00:51,505 --> 00:00:55,235
Now we are talking 
about the heart.

16
00:00:55,252 --> 00:01:02,072
Who is capable of suffering 
greater pain in the heart

17
00:01:02,072 --> 00:01:04,465
is more exalted.

18
00:01:04,483 --> 00:01:08,333
Now we’re leaving the plane
of rational thought.

19
00:01:08,347 --> 00:01:11,662
aprākṛta vastu avāṅ-mānasa-gochara

20
00:01:11,686 --> 00:01:15,899
Spiritual conception leaves
the plane of rationality.

21
00:01:15,917 --> 00:01:17,907
It’s going to contradict

22
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:21,601
what we think we know,
what we think we understand,

23
00:01:21,613 --> 00:01:24,019
what we think is happiness.

24
00:01:24,019 --> 00:01:25,618
So, Guru Maharaj 
makes this point.

25
00:01:25,618 --> 00:01:27,578
He quotes Shelley,
the poet, saying:

26
00:01:27,578 --> 00:01:36,228
“Our sweetest songs are those
that tell the saddest tales.”

27
00:01:37,007 --> 00:01:40,153
So, what are the great 
love stories?

28
00:01:40,153 --> 00:01:42,075
“Romeo and Juliet”.

29
00:01:42,075 --> 00:01:44,831
What are the great love songs?

30
00:01:44,831 --> 00:01:51,450
They are always about separation, 
heartbreaking subject matters.

31
00:01:52,405 --> 00:01:53,688
If we had—

32
00:01:53,693 --> 00:01:56,603
and let’s say speaking 
of women—

33
00:01:56,606 --> 00:01:58,706
if we had a group of women,

34
00:01:58,706 --> 00:02:03,174
and they’re watching
a heartbreaking love story,

35
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:04,845
and they’re like ...

36
00:02:04,845 --> 00:02:08,388
they’ve got tissues out,
they are crying,

37
00:02:08,388 --> 00:02:12,146
they’re watching this ... And it’s just
ripping their hearts apart,

38
00:02:12,146 --> 00:02:15,069
and some man comes in,
and he sees like ...

39
00:02:15,069 --> 00:02:17,148
[It] is a room 
full of crying women

40
00:02:17,148 --> 00:02:19,720
watching some kind of story

41
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:23,104
like movie, soap-opera, 
video, whatever it is.

42
00:02:23,104 --> 00:02:24,484
And he goes like, “Hey!

43
00:02:24,484 --> 00:02:26,601
Let me put something else on.”

44
00:02:26,601 --> 00:02:30,334
And they go like, “Stop it!!! 
Don’t move!”

45
00:02:30,334 --> 00:02:32,641
And he says, “Wait a minute.

46
00:02:32,641 --> 00:02:34,437
You’re all crying.

47
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,930
I’ll put something happy.”

48
00:02:35,930 --> 00:02:39,450
“No!!! 
Hush! Hush!..

49
00:02:39,779 --> 00:02:41,360
Quiet ...”

50
00:02:42,687 --> 00:02:45,206
So, this is what Guru Maharaj says.

51
00:02:45,216 --> 00:02:50,379
Tears are streaming down their face,
their hearts are breaking,

52
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:52,990
and they want to watch more,

53
00:02:52,990 --> 00:02:57,174
want to see the story continue.

54
00:02:57,744 --> 00:02:58,521
So he said,

55
00:02:58,521 --> 00:03:02,471
“Our sweetest songs are those
that tell the saddest tales.”

56
00:03:02,471 --> 00:03:04,735
So, ironically,

57
00:03:04,735 --> 00:03:08,502
when the heart is experiencing 
separation,

58
00:03:08,502 --> 00:03:11,722
the pain of separation,

59
00:03:11,726 --> 00:03:14,155
it reaches the greater depth

60
00:03:14,155 --> 00:03:18,271
and yields the superior
spiritual substance

61
00:03:18,271 --> 00:03:22,932
than it does
in the happy times of meeting.

62
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:25,060
So they have a saying 
that says:

63
00:03:25,074 --> 00:03:29,083
“Absence makes the heart 
grow fonder.”

64
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:33,138
So, the test is not when
the lovers are together.

65
00:03:33,138 --> 00:03:36,364
That’s never the test
is when you’re together.

66
00:03:36,381 --> 00:03:40,599
The test of love 
is when you’re apart.

67
00:03:40,599 --> 00:03:45,223
That’s when will find out 
what degree of love is there—

68
00:03:45,223 --> 00:03:47,123
when there is separation.

69
00:03:47,123 --> 00:03:50,531
Not when happy times 
in joyous union,

70
00:03:50,531 --> 00:03:53,535
but when we’re separated,
then we will see.

71
00:03:53,535 --> 00:03:57,587
And how much one, what suffering 
one is willing to endure,

72
00:03:57,589 --> 00:04:01,019
and how much sacrifice
one is willing to make

73
00:04:01,020 --> 00:04:04,778
in love, in separation 
from the beloved.

